#
# Custom recipe: SGLang v0.5.14 + our SM121 sgl-kernel patches
#                + Qwen3.6 ModelOpt mixed NVFP4 (unmerged upstream PR #27906).
#
# This is THE production 0.5.14-sm121 image, successor to sglang-0.5.13-sm121
# .recipe. Serves nvidia/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4 (now NATIVE, see below) AND
# nvidia/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-NVFP4 (PR #27906, still patched). Created 2026-06-29.
#
# Pinned to upstream tag `v0.5.14` (released 2026-06-26T22:57Z, commit 49e384ce;
# 248 commits past v0.5.13). The 0.5.13-sm121 recipe is kept for rollback.
#
# ── DELTA gegenüber sglang-0.5.13-sm121.recipe ──────────────────────────────
#   1. SGLANG_VERSION 0.5.13 → 0.5.14, SGLANG_REF v0.5.13 → v0.5.14.
#   2. DSV4 NVFP4 MoE (PR #25820) is now NATIVE in v0.5.14 (merged upstream
#      2026-06-22, listed in the v0.5.14 release notes). APPLY_DSV4_NVFP4_PR25820
#      is therefore set to 0 — re-applying a merged patch fails the in-container
#      dry-run and aborts the build. The DSV4-Flash/Pro profiles still serve off
#      this image; the source patch + tilelang-018-compat are simply no longer
#      copied/applied. (sglang-dsv4-nvfp4-pr25820.patch is retained on disk for
#      the 0.5.13 recipe and for git history.)
#   3. Qwen3.6 mixed NVFP4 (PR #27906) is STILL OPEN upstream → kept at 1.
#      ⚠️  sglang-qwen36-mixed-nvfp4-pr27906.patch was rebased onto v0.5.13 and
#      applies with `git apply` strict/fuzz=0 against THAT tag. Against v0.5.14
#      (248 commits ahead) it may no longer apply cleanly — the in-container
#      patch step gates this; if it FAILS, re-export `gh pr diff 27906` and
#      rebase onto v0.5.14 before rebuilding.
#   4. KERNELS_VERSION 0.12.3 → 0.14.1 — see the KERNELS_VERSION block below.
#   5. SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1 — see the SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD block below.
#   6. [2026-07-06] Added APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG=1 — DSV4 EAGLE-MTP on
#      this image was left non-functional by point 2 above: the marlin
#      draft-MoE branch and the TileLang 0.1.8 indexer compat fix both used to
#      ride inside sglang-dsv4-nvfp4-pr25820.patch, so retiring that patch also
#      silently dropped them. Verified via in-image source read on the running
#      0.5.14-sm121 pod (no GPU needed — pure source inspection) that neither
#      fix is present natively. Non-spec DSV4 serving is unaffected either way.
#      See the APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG block below for details.
#   7. [2026-07-09] Pin CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION — the 2026-07-06 rebuild of this
#      image silently picked up DIFFERENT nvidia-cutlass-dsl 4.5.2 wheel content
#      (same version number!): its tvm_ffi_provider passes data=[] to an
#      llvm.mlir_global_dtors() binding that lacks the parameter → every fresh
#      CuTe-DSL JIT compile ICEs ("unexpected keyword argument 'data'"), killing
#      SGLang at CUDA-graph warmup on ANY model (verified: Nemotron head +
#      Qwen3-VL vision instance; the 06-29 build of the SAME tag was fine).
#      flashinfer pins only >=4.5.0, so every rebuild re-resolves this
#      transitively.
#      [2026-07-09, revised] 4.5.3 (released 2026-07-08, OUT OF ORDER — it
#      post-dates 4.6.0 @ 2026-07-02, a late back-port hotfix) is ALSO broken,
#      but with a DIFFERENT skew: its python codegen (_gpu_ops_gen.py) calls the
#      modern generic GPUModuleOp(name, regions, …) init while the shipped native
#      _cutlass_ir only exposes the old __init__(self, operation) → "TypeError:
#      incompatible function arguments" on the first CuTe-DSL JIT (flashinfer
#      rmsnorm_cute in warmup). i.e. the 4.5.3 wheel trio (dsl / libs-base /
#      libs-cu13) is internally mismatched. Verified live: BOTH Nemotron head and
#      the Qwen3-VL vision head crashloop identically on 4.5.3 in this image.
#      Fix (VERIFIED live 2026-07-09): pin cutlass 4.6.0 (2026-07-02, clean
#      in-order release, matching python codegen + native libs) DELIBERATELY
#      PAIRED with flashinfer 0.6.14 (also 2026-07-02, see FLASHINFER_VERSION
#      block) — same-day release-mates, and 0.6.14 adds the SM120 attention fixes
#      we want. Proof: the freshly-built image's Qwen3-VL vision head reached 2/2
#      Running with 0 restarts, clearing the exact CUDA-graph warmup that crash-
#      looped on both 4.5.2-bad-bytes and 4.5.3 (choice B over the conservative
#      choice A = keep 0.6.13 + drop cutlass to 4.5.1).
#      CAVEAT on any future re-pin: NOTHING on the index is proven-good by version
#      string alone (4.5.2 shipped 2 different-byte builds; both 4.5.2-bad + 4.5.3
#      crash-looped). If a rebuild ever regresses, the ONLY reproducibly-good
#      source is the surviving 2026-06-29 image on spark1 (dangling digest
#      3ed9cc1…, cutlass 4.5.2, 15.3 GB — vs the bad 07-06 f1a951…, same "4.5.2"
#      but different _llvm_ops_gen.py bytes); extract its cutlass-dsl wheels and
#      vendor + hash-pin them. A 4.5.1+0.6.13 downgrade is a guess, not a known-
#      good — only if the vendored-bytes path is unavailable, and keep the pair
#      matched (never mix a 4.5.x cutlass with a 4.6.x-era flashinfer).
#      Re-VERIFY on any bump, in the built image (GPU required):
#        python -c "import flashinfer, torch; \
#          from flashinfer.norm import rmsnorm; \
#          x=torch.randn(4,512,device='cuda',dtype=torch.bfloat16); \
#          w=torch.randn(512,device='cuda',dtype=torch.bfloat16); \
#          print(rmsnorm(x,w).shape)"
#      (must NOT raise the GPUModuleOp TypeError / mlir_global_dtors ICE).
#      See dockerfile-cutlass-dsl-pin.patch.
#
# ⚠️  v0.5.14 is a tagged release but it is 248 commits past v0.5.13, well past
#     the 3a1417a commit the gemma-diffusion recipe was pinned to. The SM121
#     sgl-kernel source patches (sgl-kernel-sm121 / arch-prune / disable-fa3 /
#     skip-sm90-target / skip-flashmla) were last verified against the v0.5.13
#     tag (2026-06-12). They are BEST-EFFORT here and MUST pass the in-container
#     `patch --dry-run` gate. If any FAILS, regenerate it against the v0.5.14
#     source tree (and add a "<base>-mainahead.patch" sibling if the canonical
#     form no longer fits — see SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD).
#
# RUNTIME CAVEAT (unchanged from 0.5.13): the DSV4 NVFP4 path default-routes to
# moe_runner_backend=flashinfer_trtllm_routed which is not runnable on SM121
# (#26324). The DSV4 model profiles pin flashinfer_cutlass explicitly.
#
# Voraussetzungen: xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132 Base
# auf spark4 (scripts/build_pytorch_base_image.sh, siehe
# ensure_base_image_present in build_sm121_image.sh).
#
DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
TARGET=runtime

BASE_IMAGE=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132

# Override über den v0.5.14-Upstream-Pin (flashinfer_python[cu13]==0.6.12) hinaus
# auf 0.6.14 (stable, released 2026-07-02) — enthält weiterhin PR #3576
# (head_dim=512 / Gemma-4 SM120/121, Issue #3297) + NVFP4-Quant-Kernel-
# Verbesserungen (in 0.6.14 in den Release-Notes bestätigt) UND zusätzliche
# SM120/121-Attention-Fixes (FMHAv2 head_dim 256/512 + sliding-window masks) —
# direkt relevant für die GB10-Sparks. Bewusst gepaart mit cutlass-dsl 4.6.0
# unten: beide am 2026-07-02 released, also gegeneinander getestete Release-Mates
# (delta note 7). v0.5.14 pinnt im pyproject weiterhin 0.6.12, der Override bleibt
# also nötig. Roll-back-Optionen: 0.6.13 (voriger Pin) oder 0.6.12 (Upstream).
# FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.13
# FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.12
FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.14

# transformers 5.8.1 pinning — exakt SGLang v0.5.14s pyproject-Pin (==5.8.1,
# unverändert ggü. v0.5.13). NICHT isoliert über die SGLang-Ref hinaus bumpen
# (kein Perf-Nutzen — transformers ist nicht im Inferenz-Hot-Path).
TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=5.8.1

# kernels 0.14.1 — exakt SGLang v0.5.14s pyproject-Pin (kernels>=0.14.1,<0.15).
# Bumped von 0.12.3; der alte "kernels<0.13"-Pin begründete sich mit einer
# transformers-5.x/hub_kernels.py-Inkompat (LayerRepository braucht revision/
# version), die sich bei Source-Prüfung als UNBEGRÜNDET erwies — keine kernels-
# Version macht diese Args mandatory, und upstream v0.5.14 liefert transformers
# 5.8.1 + kernels 0.14.1 als getestete Kombination. PERF-NEUTRAL für SM121: der
# einzige hub-geladene SGLang-Kernel (sgl-flash-attn3) ist auf GB10 hart
# deaktiviert (_is_fa3_supported → major==9||8, GB10 ist major==12) und hat
# ohnehin keine sm_121/ARM64-Builds; der SM121-Hotpath läuft über das
# kompilierte sgl-kernel + flashinfer, nicht über den HF-Hub. 0.14.1 (nicht
# open-ended): 0.14.0 hat einen breaking repo-type-change, 0.14.1 ist der Bugfix.
KERNELS_VERSION=0.14.1

# nvidia-cutlass-dsl 4.5.3 — explicit pin, force-reinstalled late in the build
# (empty = no-op). flashinfer requires only >=4.5.0 (open-ended) AND NVIDIA has
# shipped different wheel content under the same 4.5.2 version number; the
# 2026-07-06 variant is internally inconsistent and ICEs on every fresh
# CuTe-DSL JIT compile (mlir_global_dtors 'data' kwarg — delta note 7). 4.5.3
# (2026-07-08) turned out to ALSO be broken (a different skew — see note 7), so
# we pin 4.6.0 (2026-07-02): the clean in-order release flashinfer 0.6.13 would
# naturally resolve to (>=4.5.0), with matching python codegen + native libs.
# Conservative fallback if 4.6.0 misbehaves: 4.5.1 (last pre-swap release).
# Wired via dockerfile-cutlass-dsl-pin.patch (build_sm121_image.sh step 2-cutlass).
CUTLASS_DSL_VERSION=4.6.0

# Audio multimodal deps — installed by dockerfile-audio-deps.patch (gated ARG,
# empty = no-op). Required for omni models that decode audio at runtime, e.g.
# nvidia/Nemotron-3-Nano-Omni-30B-A3B-Reasoning-NVFP4 (SGLang nano_nemotron_vl.py
# get_audio_feature → librosa; upstream SGLang does NOT install it). librosa pulls
# soundfile/audioread/numba/llvmlite as deps. Text + image/video work without this;
# only AUDIO input needs it. Empty/remove to drop the audio stack from the image.
AUDIO_DEPS="librosa"

# accelerate — baked into the image (was a runtime `pip install` in
# sglang_launch.sh). SGLang's ModelOptModelLoader (_load_modelopt_base_model)
# imports it; the upstream base image omits it, so GLM-5-NVFP4 and any
# EAGLE/speculative-decode target with a modelopt-quantized base ImportError
# without it. Installed by dockerfile-accelerate.patch (gated ARG, default
# "accelerate"). The launch-script `import accelerate || pip install` guard
# stays as belt-and-suspenders for non-baked images and becomes a fast no-op
# here. Set empty to opt out (unset also defaults to "accelerate" — the ARG
# default in the Dockerfile patch).
ACCELERATE_DEPS="accelerate"

SGLANG_VERSION=0.5.14
SGLANG_REF="v0.5.14"

# main-ahead sgl-kernel patch variant. v0.5.14 contains the mscclpp link refactor
# (dropped mscclpp_static from the common_ops_sm90/sm100 link lines + removed the
# mscclpp-build block) that landed between v0.5.13 and commit 3a1417a and broke
# the canonical sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch (Hunk #3 FAILED at 398). This
# flag makes build_sm121_image.sh install the "-mainahead" patch siblings under
# their canonical names where they exist (currently skip-sm90-target). The other
# sgl-kernel patches have no -mainahead sibling and are applied canonically; the
# in-container dry-run gates all of them — if one fails against v0.5.14,
# regenerate it against the v0.5.14 source tree. Drop this flag only if a future
# SGLANG_REF predates the mscclpp refactor.
SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1

# ── DeepSeek-V4 FlashMLA kernel: DROPPED (native SM120/121 since v0.5.13) ─────
# PR #24692 (in v0.5.13, still in v0.5.14) ships a native SM120/121 sparse-decode
# path; the 0xSero vendored sm_121a kernel + stock-flash_mla install are
# redundant (UPSTREAM_DSV4_BUGS.md §8, walls 0+6). Empty values skip the step.
FLASH_MLA_REPO=
FLASH_MLA_REF=
DSV4_KERNEL_REPO=
DSV4_KERNEL_REF=
DSV4_KERNEL_ARCH=

# ── DeepSeek-V4 NVFP4 MoE: NATIVE in v0.5.14 (PR #25820 merged) → OFF ────────
# PR #25820 merged upstream 2026-06-22 and is in the v0.5.14 tag (release notes).
# Set to 0: re-applying a merged patch fails the in-container dry-run and aborts
# the build. The DSV4 profiles still serve off this image natively. (Was =1 on
# the 0.5.13 recipe, where the PR was unmerged.)
APPLY_DSV4_NVFP4_PR25820=0

# ── DeepSeek-V4 EAGLE-MTP marlin branch + TileLang 0.1.8 indexer compat → ON ─
# Verified 2026-07-06 (in-image source read on the running 0.5.14-sm121 pod):
# the now-native HybridFp8NvFp4Config.get_quant_method hardcodes the MTP/nextn
# draft MoE layers to Mxfp4FlashinferTrtllmMoEMethod (an SM100-only TVM
# kernel) — no marlin branch — so nvidia/DeepSeek-V4-Flash-NVFP4's
# speculative_enabled: true / speculative_moe_runner_backend: marlin crashes
# on GB10 as shipped. Same verification found dsa/tilelang_kernel.py's 1D
# alloc_shared bug (breaks SGLANG_OPT_USE_TILELANG_INDEXER on TileLang 0.1.8)
# is UNCHANGED from 0.5.13. Both are small, GB10-only remainders of the old
# (now-retired) sglang-dsv4-nvfp4-pr25820.patch — rebased as standalone patches
# since the base NVFP4-MoE class they used to ship inside is native now. Gates
# dockerfile-dsv4-mtp-marlin-tilelang.patch in build_sm121_image.sh::apply_patches.
# Non-spec (no MTP) DSV4 serving is UNAFFECTED either way (native, no gate).
# Drop to 0 / delete once both fixes land upstream (marlin branch in SGLang,
# TileLang >=0.1.9 with the inject_permuted_layout 1D-shared fix).
APPLY_DSV4_MTP_MARLIN_TILELANG=1

# ── Qwen3.6 ModelOpt mixed NVFP4: upstream PR #27906, STILL OPEN → ON ────────
# Gates dockerfile-qwen36-mixed-nvfp4.patch in build_sm121_image.sh::apply_patches.
# Target: nvidia/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-NVFP4 (modelopt MIXED_PRECISION → modelopt_mixed
# + W4A16_NVFP4 lm_head/MoE/linears + wrapper-prefix + MTP). The dockerfile patch
# is trailing-context-only, so it still stacks cleanly with the DSV4 step now
# DISABLED. Set to 0 / delete once PR #27906 is merged into the pinned SGLANG_REF.
# NOTE: v0.5.14 NATIVELY merged the modelopt_mixed BASE class
# (ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig) but NOT the W4A16_NVFP4 path Qwen3.6 needs, so
# the patch still applies but had to be reconciled against that native base. The
# v0.5.14-rebased variant is sglang-qwen36-mixed-nvfp4-pr27906-mainahead.patch,
# picked up automatically via SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1 (verified git-apply clean,
# zero-fuzz, against the v0.5.14 tag). The v0.5.13 recipe keeps the original.
# Still pairs with the OPEN dispatch fix #28099 — re-validate on the live model.
APPLY_QWEN36_MIXED_NVFP4_PR27906=1

IMAGE_TAG=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.14-sm121
